My meme

I like to look at cat memes The external link to the original meme I looked at

So I thought Id do a simpler version of this original meme, which was more related to Stats 220

library(magick)
#read cat images from web
neumeme_asleep = image_read("https://cdn.pixabay.com/photo/2018/01/28/12/37/cat-3113513__480.jpg")
neumeme_awake = image_read("https://cdn.pixabay.com/photo/2017/11/14/13/06/kitty-2948404__480.jpg")

#reduce cat image size and annotate
neumeme_asleep_smaller = image_scale(neumeme_asleep, 450) %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Waasssupppp?", size = 60, font = "Monaco", gravity = "north")
neumeme_awake_smaller = image_scale(neumeme_awake, 450) %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Your data is coming !!", size = 40, font = "Optima", gravity = "north")

#create label with blank image
neumeme_label = image_blank(width = 450,
                            height = 100, 
                            color ="#3248a8") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Why you should stay awake in class",
                 color = "#FFFFFF",
                 size = 30, 
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")


#combine label and cat images underneath
  cat_vector <- c(neumeme_asleep_smaller, neumeme_awake_smaller)
  final_cat_meme <- c(neumeme_label, cat_vector) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE)


# save the image
 image_write(final_cat_meme, "my_meme.jpg")

The theme of dogs and cats fighting isnt new, but cats dont always get to win except in my animation !

library(magick)
# read the image 
dog_cat = image_read("https://cdn.pixabay.com/photo/2016/07/14/20/54/animals-1517642__480.jpg")
lightning_bolt = image_read("https://cdn.pixabay.com/photo/2017/08/01/22/38/flash-2568381__340.jpg")

# crop the image separately into smaller dog cat and lightning
dog_alone_small = image_crop(dog_cat, "200x400")
dog_alone_small = image_scale(dog_alone_small, "200")
lightning_bolt = image_scale(lightning_bolt, "x133")

# make a larger image of dog and cat
dog_cat_large = image_scale(dog_cat, 500)

# crop the larger image separately into dog vs cat
dog_alone_large = image_crop(dog_cat_large, "300x600")
cat_alone_large = image_crop(dog_cat_large, "300x800+300")

# create rroww block
rroww <- image_blank(width = 200,
                     height = 250,
                     color = "#9803fc") %>%
    image_annotate(text = "RRRRR\nOOOOO\nWWWWW\n!!!",
                   color = "#FFFFFF",
                   size = 20,
                   font = "Impact",
                   gravity = "center")
rroww <- image_scale(rroww,600)

# making loud cat row by adding rroww block to cat alone large
rroww_cat <- c(rroww, cat_alone_large)
loud_cat <- image_append(rroww_cat)


# making lightning bolt on dog by stacking lightning and dog alone small
dog_alone_small <- image_negate(dog_alone_small)
lightning_bolt_on_dog_small <- c(lightning_bolt, dog_alone_small)
lightning_bolt_on_dog_small <- image_append(lightning_bolt_on_dog_small, stack = TRUE)

# create four frames
frame1 <-dog_cat_large %>%
  image_annotate(text = "      meow...", size = 40, gravity = "center")

frame2 <-dog_cat_large %>%
  image_annotate(text = "...woof ?", size = 30, gravity = "center")

frame3 <-loud_cat %>%
  image_scale(500)

frame4 <-lightning_bolt_on_dog_small %>%
  image_annotate(text = "......whimper", size = 20, color = "#FFFFFF", gravity = "center")

# putting the frames in order in a vector
frames <- c(frame1, frame2, frame3, frame4)

# creating the animation
dog_and_cat_fight <- image_animate(frames, fps = 0.5)

# save the animation
image_write(dog_and_cat_fight, "my_animation.gif")
